{{Quote|They care. We did more than that. We passed messages. Told them about troop movements. We gave them intel, Iggs. How else do you think the rebels retook Coco-Town? That was us.|[[Streaks]], to [[Iggs]]|<ref name="Aftermath" />}}
'''CoCo Town''', also known as the '''Collective Commerce District'''<ref name="Scum and Villainy">''[[Star Wars: Scum and Villainy: Case Files on the Galaxy's Most Notorious]]''</ref> or more simply as the '''Coco District''',<ref name="Coruscant Encyclopedia">{{EncyclopediaCite|Coruscant}}</ref> was a dilapidated industrial area of the [[planet]] [[Coruscant]]. It was also the site of [[Dex's Diner]], a local [[Restaurant|eatery]] owned by [[Dexter Jettster]] during the [[Republic Era]]. Hard-working laborers visited CoCo Town to congregate at the diner.<ref name="Diner" />

During the [[Galactic Civil War]], the [[Galactic Empire]] and the [[New Republic]] fought for control of the region. Many orphans from the area formed the [[Anklebiter Brigade]], and fought alongside the rebels, sabotaging the Empire wherever possible.<ref name="Aftermath" />

